{"case_id": "case-008-d2-21", "container": "HC2", "pipeline_depth": 2, "message": "LDL 165, 10-year ASCVD 8%, no diabetes. Considering statin.", "latency_ms": 1643, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 139, "tokens_out": 59, "cost_usd": 5.625e-05, "task_success": false, "abstained": false, "answer": "Initial Assessment:\n\nThe patient is currently on Simvastatin 40mg and has been prescribed Clarithromycin for pneumonia. There is a known drug-drug interaction between Simvastatin and Clarithromycin, which increases the risk of myopathy. The patient reports no prior history of myopathy.", "tool_calls": 0, "hop_metrics": [{"hop": "vector_ingress", "latency_ms": 3, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "cache_gate", "latency_ms": 0, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "writer", "latency_ms": 1636, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 139, "tokens_out": 59, "tool_calls": 0}], "embed_count": 4, "cache_hit": true, "cache_score": 0.9782021641731262, "variant": "novel", "error": null}
{"case_id": "case-012-d6-23", "container": "HC2", "pipeline_depth": 6, "message": "CKD stage 4 (eGFR 22), osteoarthritis flare. Asking for ibuprofen 600mg TID.", "latency_ms": 5260, "llm_calls": 2, "tokens_in": 678, "tokens_out": 108, "cost_usd": 0.0001665, "task_success": true, "abstained": false, "answer": "Ibuprofen 600mg TID is not appropriate for a patient with CKD stage 4 due to the risk of accelerating renal decline. Acetaminophen, topical agents, or short-term low-dose opioids are preferred alternatives for osteoarthritis pain management [ckd_nsaid].", "tool_calls": 0, "hop_metrics": [{"hop": "vector_ingress", "latency_ms": 2, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "cache_gate", "latency_ms": 0, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "safety", "latency_ms": 2832, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 233, "tokens_out": 50, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "writer", "latency_ms": 2421, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 445, "tokens_out": 58, "tool_calls": 0}], "embed_count": 6, "cache_hit": true, "cache_score": 1.0, "variant": "novel", "error": null}
{"case_id": "case-008-d4-22", "container": "HC2", "pipeline_depth": 4, "message": "LDL 165, ASCVD 8%, no diabetes \u2014 initiate statin for primary prevention?", "latency_ms": 10246, "llm_calls": 2, "tokens_in": 261, "tokens_out": 187, "cost_usd": 0.00015135, "task_success": false, "abstained": false, "answer": "**Recommendation:**\n\nTemporarily discontinue Simvastatin 40mg for the duration of Clarithromycin therapy and for 7 days following the last dose of Clarithromycin. Clarithromycin is a strong CYP3A4 inhibitor, which significantly increases Simvastatin plasma concentrations and elevates the risk of myopathy and rhabdomyolysis. If statin therapy is deemed critical during this period, consider switching to a statin not primarily metabolized by CYP3A4 (e.g., Pravastatin or Rosuvastatin). Monitor the patient for symptoms of myopathy upon re-initiation of Simvastatin. (e.g., *FDA Drug Labeling for Simvastatin*; *Clinical Pharmacology*; *ACCF/", "tool_calls": 0, "hop_metrics": [{"hop": "vector_ingress", "latency_ms": 2, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "cache_gate", "latency_ms": 0, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "analyze", "latency_ms": 5200, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 111, "tokens_out": 41, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "writer", "latency_ms": 5039, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 150, "tokens_out": 146, "tool_calls": 0}], "embed_count": 6, "cache_hit": true, "cache_score": 1.0000001192092896, "variant": "paraphrase", "error": null}
